 up the 2008 and\n2012 elections, `obama' held a 1000:757 volume ratio over `mccain' and 1000:892\nover `romney', well short of the 1000:544 and 1000:504 volumes favoring `trump'\nover `hillary' and `biden' in the 8 weeks leading up to the 2016 and 2020\nelections. Finally, we track how only one other entity has more sustained\nultrafame than `trump' on Twitter: The K-pop (Korean pop) band BTS. We chart\nthe dramatic rise of BTS, finding their Twitter handle `@bts\\_twt' has been\nable to compete with `a' and `the'. Our findings for BTS more generally point\nto K-pop's growing economic, social, and political power.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 30 Sep 2019 23:29:59 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 11 Jan 2021 18:51:11 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 29 Oct 2021 18:44:03 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-11-02"}
