s with truly sub-cubic bounds cannot be obtained without obtaining\nsub-cubic combinatorial algorithms for Boolean Matrix Multiplication, which is\na long-standing open problem. We also show that the same hardness holds for\ngraphs of constant treewidth.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 1 Oct 2019 08:08:58 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-10-02"}
